article.headline: Pennsylvania 17, Dartmouth 10
article.story: PHILADELPHIA (AP) -- Robert Irvin passed for 227 yards and two touchdowns and Tyson Magule sparked a strong Penn defense with two interceptions as the Quakers defeated Dartmouth 17-10 in the Ivy League opener for both teams. Matt Carre had seven receptions for 87 yards, and Chris Mizell had four for 64 yards for the Quakers (1-3, 1-0 Ivy League). Mike Fritz threw for 255 yards and the Big Green's only touchdown with 37 seconds left as Dartmouth (0-3, 0-1) lost to Penn for the ninth straight time. Penn led 7-3 at the half, scoring on Irvin's 33-yard pass to Braden Lepisto, but Dartmouth's Joe Battaglia recovered a fumble of the second-half kickoff at the Penn 26. Two plays later, a 26-yard pass from Fritz to Mark Brogna put the ball at the 2, but Penn stiffened and the Big Green missed a field goal attempt. The Quakers then went 80 yards in 10 plays and scored on Irvin's 12-yard pass to Billy May with 7:31 left in the third quarter. A 20-yard field goal by Penn's Derek Zoch with 5:24 left in the game gave Penn a 17-3 lead. After Dartmouth's touchdown, the Big Green attempted an onside kick but Penn recovered it to preserve the win. Penn now holds a 41-31-2 advantage in the series.
